   "source": [
    "def is_prime(n):\n",
    "    if n == 2 or n == 3: return True\n",
    "    if n == 1 or n % 2 == 0: return False\n",
    "    if n < 9: return True\n",
    "    if n % 3 == 0: return False\n",
    "\n",
    "    r = int(n**0.5)\n",
    "    integer = 5\n",
    "\n",
    "    while integer <= r:\n",
    "        if n % integer == 0: return False\n",
    "        if n % (integer + 2) == 0: return False\n",
    "        integer += 6\n",
    "\n",
    "    return True  "
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "b5ccec13",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Since a prime $p \\geq 5$ must be congruent to either $1$ or $5$ modulo $6$, we check $n$ is divisible by every prime below $\\sqrt{n}$. If a prime $p > \\sqrt{n}$ divides $n$, then either some prime $q < \\sqrt{n}$ must divide $n$ or $p^2 > n$ must divide $n$, and the latter is a contradiction. "
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 3,
   "id": "fce6e749",
   "metadata": {
    "execution": {
